   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letterHead">
            <ab type="preprintedText">TELEGRAMS, 
               <lb/>JUVERNA LONDON." 
               <lb/>TELEPHONE, 
               <lb/>GERRARD 4703.
            </ab>
            
            <ab type="preprintedText">105, MOUNT STREET, 
               <lb/>LONDON, W.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="envelope">
            
            <p>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>To the Dean of St Hugh' College</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>in Oxford</addrLine>
               </address>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="letterBody">
            <opener>
               <dateline>5 July 1916</dateline>
               <salute>My Dear <name>Carson</name></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am confined to my bed (&amp; have been for a fortnight) by a small but quite crippling ailment. </p>
            <p> A short confidential and altogether non Committal talk might be helpful to us both â€” for I too, though by the rules of the game an
               irresponsible onlooker, am deeply concerned in this <unclear>Ll.f.</unclear> settlement (!) &amp; am going to play my part. Of Course I
               should go to you but for my unhappy plight </p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Yours ever</salute>
               <signed>Horace <name>Plunkett</name></signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>I may just say that I believe you could save 
                  the situation in <name>Ireland</name> as none other could.</p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
      </body>
